And the butt plate was cut off and rear of stock flat to attach to the stand. It was coated in an aluminum paint which has been cleaned off. The lock plate and mechanisim work great, cocks, fires. Those parts alone I could sell on gunbroker or ebay for good money. The stock does have two cartouches but cannot see them very well on the left side. A shame she got cut up to make a lamp. But still a piece of our history that should be displayed on a wall and would do so very nicely. Soldiers would lighten their rifles by cutting the stocks down and barrels too during the civil war so there is no way of knowing if that was done then or by someone years later. There is a bead sight on the end of the barrel. So it was used after being cut down. Nice wall hanger and conversation piece that looks better this way than being a lamp for sure. Would trade for 22 rifles or pistols, ruger standard, mk1s, or other old military surplus pistols

title: Want To Buy:  Sporting Goods Items and More
postcontent:
Need some quick cash?

We have an online sporting goods business, and may pay you cash or trade for the following items:

     Ammunition
          Ammo (only unopened, full boxes/cases and not reloaded by an    individual)
          Brass (only certain calibers; 380 ACP, 9x19, 40 S&W, 38 Special, 357 Magnum, 308/7.62 NATO, 223.5.56 NATO, 30.06, 12 gauge, other large rifle brass may be of interest)
          Reloading Supplies (powder, lead, dies, presses, primers, etc.)

     Archery items 

          Compound Bows (40 lbs pull or more, right or left handed)
          Take Down Recurve Bows
          Crossbows (150 lbs pull or more)
          Accessories and Parts (quivers, tools, sights, releases, arrow rests, bowfishing gear, etc.)
          Arrows, bolts and broadheads (at least 6 of the same kind, sets of 12+ preferred)

     Camping Items (very limited range of interest)
          Packs
          Tents
          Cookware (especially cast iron)
          No clothing or bedding (except military surplus)
          Feel free to ask about other items

     Firearms and Accessories
          Airguns (rifles and pistols, over 600 fps preferred)
          Rifles (AR and variants, AK, SKS, Mosin, Mauser, hunting rifles in common calibers, other rifles with rounds more powerful than a 308)
          Shotguns (mainly 12 gauge)
          Handguns (mainly Sig, Ruger, S&W, Glock, HK, FN and other high quality items, but others will be considered)
          Revolvers (mainly short barreled 38/357 or 9mm)        
          Feel free to ask about other items

     Fishing Gear     

     Military surplus items

     Quality Knives (new and used, mainly US made)

     Tools (already have most tools I need

          Hand Tools (mainly those with a lifetime guarantee, such as Craftsman, Snap-On, etc., and/or specialty tools)

          Power Tools (mainly some metal working tools like welders, mills, press, hammers, etc.)



Amount paid varies on specific item, condition and the current market.

Please, note that we will likely pay more than a pawn shop, but never pay retail.

For example, if you purchased a new item for $500, but it is now used and in good condition. We may be able to get it from the factory or a distributor for $400, and 50% is usually knocked of the value of a used item, so we may offer you $200. But, if there is very little market for the item and we cannot turn it around quickly, then we may offer less or even say that it is not something we are interested in at this time. However, certain items retain their value much better than others. We have paid up to 90% of retail before. You will just have to check with us for an estimate. Please, email us at INFO AT REAGANTACTICAL DOT COM for a quote,  or use the address at the top of this page. Please send us the following information for each item you want to sell us:

Quantity Available: (1, 2, 10, 100, etc.)
Item type: (bow, arrows, wrench set, tent, etc.)
Condition: (new in package, new, used in excellent condition, used in fair condition, etc., note scratches, dents, dings, and other damage)
Brand and Item Specifics: (Bear Whitetail II Bow)
Other Information: (Includes instructional DVD, includes a Leapers 3-9x50 scope, etc.)
Picture: (If available, not required, but helpful)

You may include the amount you want for the item, or ask about whether we have a specific item to trade with you.

Thank you,

Reagan Tactical

title: Want To Buy:  Sporting Goods and More
postcontent:
Need some quick cash?

We have an online sporting goods business, and may pay you cash or trade for the following items:

     Ammunition
          Ammo (only unopened, full boxes/cases and not reloaded by an    individual)
          Brass (only certain calibers; 380 ACP, 9x19, 40 S&W, 38 Special, 357 Magnum, 308/7.62 NATO, 223.5.56 NATO, 30.06, 12 gauge, other large rifle brass may be of interest)
          Reloading Supplies (powder, lead, dies, presses, primers, etc.)

     Archery items 

          Compound Bows (40 lbs pull or more, right or left handed)
          Take Down Recurve Bows
          Crossbows (150 lbs pull or more)
          Accessories and Parts (quivers, tools, sights, releases, arrow rests, bowfishing gear, etc.)
          Arrows, bolts and broadheads (at least 6 of the same kind, sets of 12+ preferred)

     Camping Items (very limited range of interest)
          Packs
          Tents
          Cookware (especially cast iron)
          No clothing or bedding (except military surplus)
          Feel free to ask about other items

     Firearms and Accessories
          Airguns (rifles and pistols, over 600 fps preferred)
          Rifles (AR and variants, AK, SKS, Mosin, Mauser, hunting rifles in common calibers, other rifles with rounds more powerful than a 308)
          Shotguns (mainly 12 gauge)
          Handguns (mainly Sig, Ruger, S&W, Glock, HK, FN and other high quality items, but others will be considered)
          Revolvers (mainly short barreled 38/357 or 9mm)        
          Feel free to ask about other items

     Fishing Gear     

     Military surplus items

     Quality Knives (new and used, mainly US made)

     Tools (already have most tools I need

          Hand Tools (mainly those with a lifetime guarantee, such as Craftsman, Snap-On, etc., and/or specialty tools)

          Power Tools (mainly some metal working tools like welders, mills, press, hammers, etc.)



Amount paid varies on specific item, condition and the current market.

Please, note that we will likely pay more than a pawn shop, but never pay retail.

For example, if you purchased a new item for $500, but it is now used and in good condition. We may be able to get it from the factory or a distributor for $400, and 50% is usually knocked of the value of a used item, so we may offer you $200. But, if there is very little market for the item and we cannot turn it around quickly, then we may offer less or even say that it is not something we are interested in at this time. However, certain items retain their value much better than others. We have paid up to 90% of retail before. You will just have to check with us for an estimate. Please, email us at INFO AT REAGANTACTICAL DOT COM for a quote,  or use the address at the top of this page. Please send us the following information for each item you want to sell us:

Quantity Available: (1, 2, 10, 100, etc.)
Item type: (bow, arrows, wrench set, tent, etc.)
Condition: (new in package, new, used in excellent condition, used in fair condition, etc., note scratches, dents, dings, and other damage)
Brand and Item Specifics: (Bear Whitetail II Bow)
Other Information: (Includes instructional DVD, includes a Leapers 3-9x50 scope, etc.)
Picture: (If available, not required, but helpful)

You may include the amount you want for the item, or ask about whether we have a specific item to trade with you.

Thank you,

Reagan Tactical

 This 'MARLIN 200' has a beautifully colored case hardened receiver, a nicely blued barrel, and the metal to wood fit is awesome.

 The OAL of the Barrel is 27.5", is chambered for 12 Ga. shells up to 3", and it has a Modified Choke.

title: For Trade:  Museum Piece-- Authentic all matching original WW2 German Luger
postcontent:
Alright collector's I have something above the rest for you.  I have a 1937 S/42 Mauser made German Luger in 9mm. This gun is COMPLETELY original with ALL matching numbers (small parts, grips, etc) and yes I even have the original magazine with the matching numbers and stamp as well. As you can see for yourself this gun is in amazing condition, and surpasses the quality of most I have seen.  The gun also comes with another magazine and an authentic Luger holster made in 1940. Just remember this gun is like a classic hot rod, you won't be able to go out and just find them, and good examples like mine only appreciate in value every year, and are becoming harder and HARDER to find, all the stockpiles and secret caches are gone and most of the surviving pieces are mismatched numbers, don't have all the original pieces, or look like they were dragged behind a truck for miles. 
DO YOUR HOMEWORK please before offering me, these things go around $1500 in half the quality of what I have, look at all the sites and speak to people, with all matching numbers, the original magazine, and in this condition most people ask between $2000-$2500 as this is the Mauser made S/42 that is the sought after model and the one I have is what every collector looks for in every aspect (condition, quality, desirability).

Don't be afraid to shoot me an offer I am looking for a Springfield M1A (I will trade straight across for any model M1a) , AR-10's, AK's, long distance shooters (308's with bull barrels, etc) quality handguns (sig sauer, springfield xdm, etc) or even a trained bird dog, or a couple good pupppies to train myself. these are some ideas of things I am looking for, but as always I am open to trades and offers just let me know what you have, and the worst I will say is no.  If you prefer to just purchase it that is fine, just shoot me a reasonable offer and we will talk her out.  Thank you

In closing, please ONLY SERIOUS INQUIRIES I am a military man and a single father, I have no time to waste and would appreciate it if you are unsure to just wait to contact me until you are sure, thanks.

postcontent:
This is a 95% condition 1960's High Standard Flite King 20 gauge pump action shotgun with the Sears brand label.

This was inherited by me from the original owner in 2007. I'm guessing that it was manufactured 1964-1966. It precedes the Gun Control Act of 1968 and has no serial number.

Bluing is in near-new condition except minor marks from the slide reciprocating. Stock has minor marks from going in/out of a gun cabinet.

A vey light weight gun with a 28 inch modified choke barrel. Plain barrel with no rib.

I fired a few shells through it to make sure that it shoots. Other than that, this hasn't seen the light of day since the mid 1970's.

The rubber recol pad is in good shape but is rock-hard from age.

100% original. An excellent choice as an alternative to a soul-less Wal-Mart Rem 870 or Mossberg 500.

This is a  very pretty gun with character.

Sorry, I'm not interested in trades.
